WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.412
NARRATOR:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.587 --> 00:05.919
-Who do you think you are?
-Tess Mercer.

00:06.090 --> 00:09.878
I'm now the acting CEO of LuthorCorp
and all its subsidiaries.

00:10.260 --> 00:12.421
-Will you marry me?
AGENT: Don't move.

00:12.596 --> 00:14.382
Chloe Sullivan, you're under arrest.

00:14.556 --> 00:15.716
Jimmy, get Clark!

00:15.891 --> 00:19.383
Chloe Sullivan was never arrested
by the Department of Domestic Security.

00:19.561 --> 00:21.847
She's at a research compound
in Montana.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.887
Called Black Creek.

00:25.275 --> 00:27.357
This was retrieved at the excavation site.

00:27.528 --> 00:29.735
TESS: The Montana facility?
KAT: Completely dismantled.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.520
The guests have been reassimilated.

00:31.699 --> 00:33.189
I'm so glad you're okay.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.107
Jimmy.

00:36.328 --> 00:38.068
Yes.

00:40.624 --> 00:44.367
I've been holding on to a life on this farm
that hasn't existed for years.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.285
I'll see you bright and early Monday.

00:46.463 --> 00:49.250
You're looking at the newest recruit
to the Daily Planet.

00:49.425 --> 00:50.881
We're gonna be neighbors, Lane.

01:08.652 --> 01:10.643
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

01:22.833 --> 01:23.913
[SIGHS]

01:27.337 --> 01:28.497
[CLARK CLEARS THROAT]

01:29.506 --> 01:32.839
Wow, big points for punctuality,
Smallville...

01:33.010 --> 01:34.841
...what's with
the wardrobe malfunction?

01:35.012 --> 01:36.377
What?

01:37.181 --> 01:38.591
This is a nice shirt.

01:38.766 --> 01:40.006
[SCOFFS]

01:40.184 --> 01:42.470
Human Resources is gonna be
down here...

01:42.644 --> 01:47.183
...and you do not wanna meet them
looking like Brawny Lumberjack.

01:49.151 --> 01:50.812
Hold on.

01:54.031 --> 01:56.693
Hey. Personal space, Lane. Remember?

01:56.867 --> 01:57.856
[SIGHS]

01:58.035 --> 02:00.196
60 here needs some roadside assistance.

02:00.370 --> 02:02.452
Let me borrow your spare.

02:02.623 --> 02:04.329
Come with me.

02:04.541 --> 02:06.748
-Don't tell me I have to wear a tie?
-Dress for success.

02:06.919 --> 02:09.661
No time for the men's room.
Let's change in here.

02:09.838 --> 02:14.127
-A phone booth is not exactly private.
-Buming daylight hours, Clark. Change.

02:15.093 --> 02:17.505
Lucky for you it's a slow news day
and I was at my desk.

02:17.679 --> 02:21.547
You could have spent your entire career
being nicknamed Farm Boy or Flannel Man.

02:21.725 --> 02:23.716
WOMAN:
Hey, Lois.

02:23.894 --> 02:27.887
Trust me, the news game can be brutal. You
do not want to bomb on your ﬁrst day. Hi.

02:29.483 --> 02:32.520
So how do I look?

02:36.740 --> 02:38.025
Um....

02:40.410 --> 02:41.911
Good.

02:43.956 --> 02:46.493
[EXPLOSION]

02:46.667 --> 02:49.204
[CROWD SHOUTING]

02:53.006 --> 02:55.622
So much for the slow news day.

02:57.135 --> 02:58.420
Clark?

02:59.763 --> 03:01.424
[CROWD SHOUTING]

03:11.441 --> 03:13.773
[ALL SHOUTING]

03:13.944 --> 03:16.310
WOMAN:
Down here!

03:24.246 --> 03:26.953
[ALL SHOUTING]

03:27.124 --> 03:29.615
MAN: Go ahead.
CLARK: Get away from the bus.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.958
Okay. Come on.

03:32.129 --> 03:33.494
[WOMAN COUGHING]

03:33.672 --> 03:35.458
MAN:
Let's go.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.848
[SIRENS WAILING]

03:50.272 --> 03:52.433
[CROWD CHATTERING]

04:02.951 --> 04:05.488
Guess this must be my stop.

05:00.717 --> 05:03.049
[SIRENS WAILING]

05:07.557 --> 05:10.890
[FIREFIGHTERS CHATTERING]

05:11.061 --> 05:13.723
[CROWD CHATTERING]

05:18.485 --> 05:20.396
[COUGHING]

05:26.910 --> 05:28.866
[GASPING]

05:30.497 --> 05:32.078
CHLOE:
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

05:32.249 --> 05:34.911
Can somebody help us over here, please?

05:35.085 --> 05:36.074
[BETTE GASPING]

05:36.545 --> 05:38.706
CHLOE:
Over here.

05:41.717 --> 05:42.832
[BETTE COUGHING]

05:43.010 --> 05:45.001
-Hi. I don't know.
-Was she on the bus?

05:45.887 --> 05:47.093
Can you do a--?

05:47.764 --> 05:49.755
Hold on to this for me?

05:49.933 --> 05:52.265
-What's your name?
-Bette.

05:52.436 --> 05:55.644
You inhaled a lot of smoke, Bette.
We're gonna give you fresh air.

05:55.814 --> 05:58.180
Take slow, deep breaths.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.098
Try to stay calm, okay?

06:00.819 --> 06:03.561
I'm gonna check you over.
Tell me if anything hurts.

06:05.949 --> 06:07.940
CHLOE:
Hang in there, Bette.

06:09.453 --> 06:10.613
It's okay.

06:10.954 --> 06:12.785
You're doing great.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.455
You too.

06:16.126 --> 06:17.536
Thank God you heard me.

06:18.754 --> 06:20.244
You're hard to miss.

06:20.422 --> 06:21.457
Look at me.

06:21.631 --> 06:24.168
Apart from breathing in all that smoke,
you're gonna be okay.

06:24.342 --> 06:28.301
We should still get you to Met General
to be sure. Think you can make it to my rig?

06:30.432 --> 06:31.797
-Can you grab my bag?
-Yeah.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.590
-Thanks. Uh...?
-Chloe.

06:33.769 --> 06:36.761
Davis. You make a good wingman, Chloe.
Or wingperson.

06:37.022 --> 06:38.933
Thank you for your help.

06:40.150 --> 06:42.687
Now, straight to the hospital, okay?

06:42.944 --> 06:44.525
You're gonna be okay.

06:44.696 --> 06:48.063
-You'll be all right. You mind taking a look?
-Yes.

06:48.450 --> 06:49.986
There was a woman with red hair.

06:50.327 --> 06:53.160
I helped her out of the bus.
Do you know if she's all right?

06:53.330 --> 06:57.539
People have been coming in and out but the
most seriously injured are at the hospital.

06:57.709 --> 06:59.620
-You should try there.
-Thank you.

06:59.795 --> 07:01.331
Hey. Clark.

07:02.005 --> 07:03.666
Chloe?

07:04.591 --> 07:06.707
-Are you all right?
-Yeah. I just got here.

07:06.885 --> 07:09.968
I just helped this girl that was on that bus.
What happened?

07:10.138 --> 07:13.630
I heard there was a bomb on the bus.
I haven't had a chance to check it out.

07:13.809 --> 07:15.970
Even a dress shirt
can't hide the hero in you.

07:16.144 --> 07:17.520
Heck of a ﬁrst day.

07:17.687 --> 07:20.019
That's why I'm there.
So I can help more people.

07:20.190 --> 07:23.603
Working at the Daily Planet,
I'II hear about every crisis as it happens.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.392
I just wish you were there with me.

07:25.570 --> 07:28.653
You know,
now that Lex isn't running things--

07:28.824 --> 07:29.859
Yeah. Heh.

07:30.033 --> 07:33.025
I've spent my entire life
praying to the gods ofjournalism.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.319
It might be kind of nice
to try something new.

07:35.497 --> 07:36.782
See how it feels.

07:36.957 --> 07:38.618
Now you're ready for a change?

07:40.210 --> 07:41.495
Actually, uh...

07:41.670 --> 07:42.830
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

07:43.004 --> 07:44.619
...it's pretty big changes.

07:44.798 --> 07:45.958
[SIGHS]

07:46.550 --> 07:49.508
Apparently the goddess of journalism
is wondering where I am.

07:49.678 --> 07:54.138
With Lois on the case, it's gonna get harder
to duck away to save the day.

07:54.558 --> 07:56.924
If I could hide my secret from you,
I can handle your cousin.

07:57.102 --> 07:59.593
Huh. Good luck with that.

07:59.813 --> 08:01.223
I gotta go.

08:01.398 --> 08:04.640
Uh, tell Lois that I said
to take it easy on you.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.325
Whoa, Clark, what happened?
Are you okay?

08:19.499 --> 08:21.364
Why? Were you worried about me?

08:21.543 --> 08:23.829
Uh, no. I'm trying to chase down
a lead on this story.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.837
I don't wanna
have to chase after you too.

08:27.424 --> 08:30.507
Hey, did you happen to hear anything
while you were out there?

08:30.677 --> 08:34.511
Actually, I did. Police think the bomb
misﬁred, since there weren't casualties.

08:34.806 --> 08:37.263
Didn't feel like a misﬁre to me.

08:37.684 --> 08:40.471
All right. Who's your source?

08:41.479 --> 08:43.390
I'm sorry, Lois. I didn't get a name.

08:43.565 --> 08:45.931
I was too busy, you know,
helping people?

08:46.943 --> 08:48.899
Okay. Rule number one:

08:49.070 --> 08:51.277
Always know your source.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.196
I understand.

08:53.366 --> 08:55.197
Look, if you're gonna teach a class...

08:55.368 --> 08:59.031
...on Lois Lane's Rules of Reporting
I think I'd rather read the CliffsNotes.

08:59.414 --> 09:01.905
Boss wants to see you. Now.

09:03.460 --> 09:05.951
Okay, my ﬁrst ofﬁcial meeting
with our latest leader.

09:06.129 --> 09:08.120
Not you. Kent.

09:08.798 --> 09:09.833
Oh.

09:10.008 --> 09:11.873
Well, you're gonna
wanna clean yourself up.

09:12.052 --> 09:14.839
Uh, rule number two,
always make a good ﬁrst impression...

09:15.013 --> 09:16.969
...and don't screw up with the boss.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.138
I think that's two rules.

09:20.435 --> 09:23.097
Whatever. Try not to get ﬁred
on your ﬁrst day, okay?

09:25.482 --> 09:26.722
[SIGHS]

09:36.159 --> 09:37.899
MAN:
Go right in.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.822
TESS:
Have a seat, Mr. Kent.

09:54.010 --> 09:56.843
Tess Mercer, acting CEO of LuthorCorp.

09:57.973 --> 09:59.429
You're my boss?

09:59.599 --> 10:02.341
You weren't this shy
when l was the damsel in distress.

10:02.519 --> 10:04.931
Don't tell me you're intimidated
by a powerful woman.

10:05.105 --> 10:08.313
No, I just-- I'm surprised
to see you back at work so soon.

10:08.483 --> 10:11.600
Well, I have big shoes to ﬁll,
and the paramedic said I was ﬁne.

10:13.280 --> 10:14.395
It's unusual, isn't it?

10:14.572 --> 10:17.484
For the new CEO of LuthorCorp
to be taking the bus to work?

10:17.784 --> 10:19.320
I'm going green.

10:19.494 --> 10:22.361
You know, doing what I can
to save the planet.

10:22.539 --> 10:26.248
But for the sake of the shareholders,
let's keep that between ourselves. Hmm?

10:26.710 --> 10:29.167
Seems we were destined to meet.

10:29.421 --> 10:32.003
I already had you
on my "to do" list today.

10:36.386 --> 10:39.048
Lex told me all about you.

10:41.474 --> 10:42.589
[CHUCKLES]

10:42.767 --> 10:45.258
Well, not much to tell, really.

10:45.812 --> 10:49.225
Hmm. He said you have a thing
for saving people.

10:49.399 --> 10:51.230
After this morning, I'd say that's true.

10:52.193 --> 10:54.104
Ever since Lex's disappearance...

10:54.279 --> 10:56.895
...l have used all of LuthorCorp's resources
to ﬁnd him.

10:57.198 --> 11:00.656
-Do you have any leads?
-The world's a big place.

11:00.827 --> 11:04.240
I was hoping his good friend
could tell me where to look.

11:05.540 --> 11:06.575
[SIGHS]

11:07.250 --> 11:10.287
The Lex Luthor that I knew
disappeared years ago.

11:10.462 --> 11:13.169
It's been a long time
since we were friends.

11:14.341 --> 11:16.206
I don't know what happened to him.

11:18.636 --> 11:20.422
Fair enough.

11:21.097 --> 11:24.089
But if you do think of something,
please give me a call.

11:24.684 --> 11:26.470
And Clark...

11:27.520 --> 11:30.182
...you were extraordinary out there.

11:31.107 --> 11:33.098
Thank you for saving my life.

11:41.076 --> 11:44.489
I saw how this job consumed Lex's life.

11:45.121 --> 11:47.954
I'd hate to see
the same thing happen to yours.

11:58.468 --> 11:59.583
Handsome.

11:59.761 --> 12:01.297
And a liar.

12:01.471 --> 12:02.881
He's hiding something.

12:03.848 --> 12:05.224
I'll have someone watch him.

12:05.392 --> 12:07.974
No. I'll keep an eye
on this one personally.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.033
-Hey.
CHLOE: Hey.

12:33.211 --> 12:36.999
Doc says I'm okay. But I feel like
I just threw down with a cardinal cold.

12:37.173 --> 12:40.210
I ﬁgured you'd be hungry.
Unfortunately, it's Meatloaf Mondays.

12:40.385 --> 12:41.921
But I did score you some curly fries.

12:42.095 --> 12:45.053
Are you kidding?
Hot food's good any day of the week.

12:45.223 --> 12:46.804
Thanks.

12:46.975 --> 12:50.718
I, uh-- I'm surprised
your parents aren't here.

12:52.439 --> 12:57.274
It's really cool what you did for me, but
doesn't mean I have to tell you my story.

12:58.486 --> 13:00.022
I wasn't asking.

13:02.490 --> 13:03.991
I haven't seen them in years.

13:04.159 --> 13:07.367
I'm kind of in between homes right now.

13:11.541 --> 13:15.159
You know, why don't I grab you a soda
to wash that down.

13:20.550 --> 13:22.131
Hey.

13:22.343 --> 13:24.299
-Davis, hi.
-How's she doing?

13:24.471 --> 13:26.837
Uh, she got a clean bill of health.

13:27.015 --> 13:30.883
But, uh, I just found out
that she's a street kid.

13:31.060 --> 13:35.178
So I was gonna drop her off
at the city shelter tonight.

13:36.065 --> 13:37.601
She's a 15-year-old girl, Chloe.

13:37.775 --> 13:40.482
You think she's gonna be safe
in a Metropolis shelter?

13:40.653 --> 13:42.564
Not too streetwise, are you?

13:42.739 --> 13:44.775
I was just trying to help.

13:44.949 --> 13:46.814
If you have any ideas...

13:46.993 --> 13:49.325
...please step up and do something.

13:58.880 --> 14:02.088
So I hear that you need a place to stay.

14:07.555 --> 14:09.295
Not really.

14:10.600 --> 14:12.136
But if you did, I have a friend.

14:12.310 --> 14:14.767
And she runs a home and it's pretty nice.

14:14.938 --> 14:16.519
Is she some kind of religious nut?

14:16.689 --> 14:18.304
I don't really roll with the holy.

14:18.483 --> 14:21.566
It's not like that. She helps girls learn
some skills, score a job.

14:21.736 --> 14:23.692
I can get you an application.

14:24.113 --> 14:25.523
Or you can forget it.

14:25.698 --> 14:26.983
It's your choice.

14:28.117 --> 14:31.701
Look, Bette, you can stay with me tonight
if you need to.

14:33.790 --> 14:35.030
You're nice, Chloe.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.448
Kind of like a Girl Scout.

14:37.001 --> 14:39.162
I don't wanna be your latest merit badge.

14:39.546 --> 14:43.380
Okay, I'm gonna take my Thin Mints
and head home.

14:43.550 --> 14:45.962
Thought you might want a safe place
to stay tonight.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.172
But would I still be a free agent?

14:50.765 --> 14:53.757
As long as you promise
to think about Davis' offer.

14:59.482 --> 15:00.813
Okay, I'm in.

15:01.276 --> 15:03.187
Great. Let's go.

15:08.866 --> 15:11.027
CLARK: That new boss,
she came out of nowhere, huh?

15:11.202 --> 15:14.319
LOIS: You tell me. You're the one
who just spent quality time with her.

15:14.497 --> 15:16.488
CLARK: She just wanted to welcome me
aboard.

15:16.666 --> 15:19.908
Don't try to keep secrets from me.
Tess Mercer is a pit bull in Prada.

15:20.086 --> 15:22.327
There's no way she'd roll out
the mat for a oopyboy...

15:22.505 --> 15:24.336
...no matter how charming his smile is.

15:24.507 --> 15:26.543
You think I have a charming smile?

15:26.718 --> 15:29.551
I think you're about to lose some teeth
if you don't tell me.

15:29.721 --> 15:34.010
-Lois, you sound like a jealous girlfriend.
-Jealous, of you?

15:34.183 --> 15:38.347
Please, that would be like Willie Mays
being jealous of a bat boy.

15:39.022 --> 15:40.978
Watch and learn.

15:44.527 --> 15:46.028
Hi.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.572
Lois Lane, Daily Planet.

15:48.740 --> 15:50.947
-Care to show me around?
-No press allowed.

15:57.040 --> 15:58.029
Swing and a miss.

15:58.207 --> 15:59.196
[LOIS CHUCKLES]

15:59.375 --> 16:01.707
I'm just getting started.

16:06.466 --> 16:08.002
Excuse me.

16:08.176 --> 16:10.167
Do you like baseball?

16:10.345 --> 16:13.712
Who's your favorite player? Because
I can get you a signed photograph...

16:13.890 --> 16:16.597
...of anyone you want if you just do me
this little favor.

16:16.768 --> 16:18.633
OFFICER:
Sorry, ma'am. No one is allowed in.

16:19.062 --> 16:22.646
LOIS: What's your name, ofﬁcer?
OFFICER: Ofﬁcer Darren.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.933
CSI AGENT 1: Double checked?
It's got to be a mistake.

16:27.111 --> 16:28.362
CSI AGENT 2:
No mistake, sir.

16:28.529 --> 16:30.781
We haven 't found
one shred of explosive material.

16:30.948 --> 16:33.439
There's no residue, no detonator,
there's nothing.

16:33.618 --> 16:35.074
There's no bomb in this bus.

16:35.244 --> 16:36.324
LOIS:
Wake up, Smallville.

16:36.496 --> 16:39.533
That cop's about as stiff
as his starched uniform. Let's move on.

16:39.707 --> 16:41.618
Lois, I just heard there was no bomb.

16:46.506 --> 16:48.417
That doesn't look like
the engine overheating.

16:48.591 --> 16:51.708
Look, we need talk to somebody
who was on the bus.

16:51.928 --> 16:54.590
Chloe called. She's helping a homeless girl
who was there.

16:54.764 --> 16:56.925
Maybe you could ask her.
I'll track the others.

16:57.100 --> 16:58.931
The thing is, not so good with the kids.

16:59.102 --> 17:02.265
Why don't you take Little Orphan Annie,
and I'll do the rest.

17:13.074 --> 17:15.565
Bette, thank you so much.

17:15.743 --> 17:17.904
It's just a grilled cheese, no big.

17:18.079 --> 17:21.071
All this takeout, I thought
you could use something home-cooked.

17:21.249 --> 17:22.409
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

17:24.293 --> 17:27.035
It's okay. It's just, uh, my friend Clark.
Don't worry about it.

17:27.213 --> 17:28.794
What's up?

17:29.132 --> 17:31.623
Wait, I remember you.
You helped me get off the bus.

17:31.801 --> 17:34.042
Yeah. I'm glad you're okay, Bette.

17:34.220 --> 17:36.176
Do you mind
if I ask you a few questions?

17:37.765 --> 17:40.302
Did you see anything before the blast?
Anything unusual?

17:40.476 --> 17:41.886
Anything strange?

17:42.770 --> 17:45.477
-What, are you like a cop or something?
-C|ark.

17:45.648 --> 17:47.149
She's been through a lot today.

17:47.316 --> 17:50.729
-What's going on?
-Police say there's no evidence of a bomb.

17:50.903 --> 17:54.737
I think someone with a meteor power
may have caused the blast.

17:55.992 --> 17:58.324
What's a meteor power?

17:59.162 --> 18:02.654
Uh, sometimes people develop
special abilities...

18:02.832 --> 18:06.666
...after being exposed
to a certain type of meteor rock.

18:06.836 --> 18:08.701
Tommy.

18:08.963 --> 18:10.328
Another street kid.

18:10.506 --> 18:13.714
He told me he found this weird rock
a couple of days ago...

18:13.885 --> 18:17.002
...and now, whenever he gets angry,
things heat up.

18:17.180 --> 18:18.886
I thought he was messing with me.

18:19.056 --> 18:20.512
We got into a ﬁght today.

18:20.683 --> 18:23.516
He was being a jerk. I ran onto the bus
to get away from him.

18:23.686 --> 18:25.927
-Where can I ﬁnd him?
-I know where he hangs.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.686
I can remember how to get there.

18:27.857 --> 18:30.599
Wait. This guy sounds dangerous.
I don't think you should go.

18:30.777 --> 18:34.520
Well, I'll wait in the car.
I can point him out to you.

18:34.947 --> 18:35.982
[DOOR OPENS]

18:39.118 --> 18:41.359
MAN:
One-eighty, man.

18:41.996 --> 18:43.327
Yeah, bro.

18:43.498 --> 18:45.409
He's over there, sitting down.

18:47.293 --> 18:48.624
CLARK:
I saw him earlier.

18:48.795 --> 18:51.161
He was running away from the bus.

18:56.177 --> 18:58.042
Tommy?

18:59.347 --> 19:01.383
It's all right. I just wanna talk.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.265
Tommy, it's okay.

19:07.188 --> 19:08.519
Stay here.

19:11.150 --> 19:12.526
Tommy.

19:12.693 --> 19:14.274
Tommy.

19:14.445 --> 19:17.061
-You don't have to be afraid.
TOMMY: Get away from me!

19:17.323 --> 19:19.735
It'll be okay, Tommy. I promise.

19:19.909 --> 19:21.900
No. No. No. You're lying!

19:22.078 --> 19:24.490
Just be calm.
There's no reason for anyone to get hurt.

19:24.664 --> 19:26.245
Get away from me!

19:26.415 --> 19:28.576
Bette, stay back, he could be dangerous.

19:28.751 --> 19:30.287
How can you do this to me?

19:30.586 --> 19:33.498
Just-- Just stay away.

19:37.760 --> 19:39.751
Tommy!

19:55.570 --> 19:57.106
CLARK:
He was scared, Lois.

19:57.280 --> 19:59.987
He didn't mean to hurt anyone.
Couldn't control his powers.

20:00.408 --> 20:03.320
He blew up a bus, Clark.
Almost killed a lot of people.

20:03.494 --> 20:05.030
I'd say this was textbook karma.

20:08.207 --> 20:09.413
[RECORDER BEEPS]

20:09.584 --> 20:12.667
-Thanks.
-You didn't tell me you were recording that.

20:12.837 --> 20:16.705
Don't get your tights in a twist, Smallville.
I'll just refer to you as sources say.

20:16.883 --> 20:21.297
Besides, if I'm gonna write Tommy
was a human bomb, I need scientiﬁc proof.

20:21.470 --> 20:24.837
We could check the autopsy report.
See how much meteor rock was in him.

20:25.016 --> 20:29.134
The coroner won't release it
if it's part of an ongoing investigation.

20:30.313 --> 20:33.897
But I bet we could ﬁnd a copy
lying around the hospital.

20:34.066 --> 20:35.931
CLARK:
By ﬁnd, I'm assuming you mean steal?

20:36.193 --> 20:39.185
Rule number three,
do whatever it takes to get the story.

20:39.363 --> 20:40.899
You should be writing these down.

20:41.073 --> 20:43.485
Lois, be careful.
There's some lines you shouldn't cross.

20:43.659 --> 20:45.945
The only line I'm worried about
is a byline.

20:46.203 --> 20:48.364
And so should you.
We're in this together.

20:48.539 --> 20:50.120
You wanna share a byline with me?

20:50.291 --> 20:51.497
Oh, God, no.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.874
But I got you the obit.

20:54.045 --> 20:55.660
-Tommy's obituary?
-Absolutely.

20:55.838 --> 20:57.078
You helped break the story...

20:57.256 --> 20:59.497
...so you get to commemorate the kid
in 10 lines or less.

20:59.675 --> 21:00.881
[SIGHS]

21:01.052 --> 21:04.544
Don't be so squeamish.
Most of us got started writing want ads.

21:04.722 --> 21:08.681
You know what, there was a time
when I would've killed for an obit.

21:10.227 --> 21:11.888
Are you coming?

21:12.980 --> 21:13.969
[DOOR OPENS]

21:14.148 --> 21:15.263
[SIGHS]

21:16.651 --> 21:17.857
[DOOR OPENS]

21:18.027 --> 21:19.142
CHLOE:
Oh.

21:19.320 --> 21:21.026
[LIGHTS TINKLING]

21:21.197 --> 21:23.404
[CHLOE GRUNTING]

21:28.245 --> 21:30.827
DAVIS: You know, if you just reach
a little bit higher...

21:31.540 --> 21:33.155
...you're gonna need an ambulance.

21:33.334 --> 21:35.791
Guess I'm lucky
there's a paramedic in the building.

21:36.545 --> 21:39.503
Yeah, well, you asked me
to bring over this application.

21:43.928 --> 21:45.884
Ahem. Give me.

21:46.681 --> 21:48.842
Oh, I did talk to my friend.

21:49.016 --> 21:53.601
And she says that there is a spot
open at the home for Bette.

21:54.063 --> 21:56.054
That's great.

21:59.276 --> 22:02.643
She could really use some good news
right now.

22:02.989 --> 22:05.822
Her day got even worse a while ago
and she needed some space.

22:05.992 --> 22:07.027
So I came here.

22:13.874 --> 22:14.954
Thank you.

22:15.126 --> 22:17.742
At least she had a place to stay,
thanks to you.

22:18.337 --> 22:20.077
[CHLOE CLEARS THROAT]

22:20.256 --> 22:21.962
Thanks.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.176
Isis Foundation.

22:27.346 --> 22:30.804
So what, Adopt a Pyramid,
Save a Sphinx, that kind of thing?

22:30.975 --> 22:35.093
Heh, cute. Uh, actually, it's more like
a counseling center.

22:35.271 --> 22:38.263
I'm house-sitting
until she ﬁnds someone to take it over.

22:38.607 --> 22:41.474
I'm surprised I haven't heard of it.
The hospital sends out updates...

22:41.652 --> 22:43.517
...on all the mental health facilities.

22:43.696 --> 22:45.937
Well, she has very speciﬁc clients.

22:46.115 --> 22:50.279
People with, uh, special skills that are
sometimes a little dangerous.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.742
You mean like meteor types?

22:54.290 --> 22:57.657
I drive an ambulance in Metropolis, Chloe.
I've seen a lot of things.

22:57.835 --> 23:01.123
At least enough to know
that they could use the help.

23:03.257 --> 23:05.293
Have you ever thought
about helping them?

23:05.468 --> 23:07.800
-No, I don't—
-I saw you with Bette today.

23:07.970 --> 23:11.383
You cared enough
to take her under your wing. That's rare.

23:11.557 --> 23:13.639
And think how hard it must be...

23:13.809 --> 23:16.300
...for meteor people
to ﬁnd someone they can trust.

23:17.146 --> 23:18.977
But am I streetwise enough?

23:19.148 --> 23:21.309
Okay. Forget what I said earlier.

23:21.484 --> 23:24.021
I can come off a little strong.

23:24.195 --> 23:26.902
That's okay. At least now I understand
where it comes from.

23:28.032 --> 23:29.613
Understand how?

23:29.784 --> 23:31.615
Well, I Googled you.

23:31.786 --> 23:35.244
I read an interview you gave about
running away from foster homes as a kid.

23:35.414 --> 23:36.950
You researched me?

23:37.124 --> 23:38.580
[CHUCKLES]

23:38.751 --> 23:40.787
Well, I always kind of wanted
my own stalker.

23:40.961 --> 23:43.748
Ha, ha. It isn't like that, Davis.
It's just that--

23:43.923 --> 23:47.541
No, really. I used to be a reporter,
and so I have a serious...

23:47.718 --> 23:49.583
...curiosity complex.

23:50.054 --> 23:52.340
-Okay. Yeah.
-And I'm engaged.

23:55.684 --> 23:57.766
You're the ﬁrst person I've told
about that.

23:57.937 --> 23:59.848
Well, um-- Congratulations.

24:00.022 --> 24:03.389
That's a very unique engagement ring.

24:04.276 --> 24:08.565
Uh, well, it's the story behind the ring
that really makes it special.

24:08.906 --> 24:12.524
I went away for a little while,
and he never gave up on me.

24:14.245 --> 24:15.735
Well, Chloe...

24:15.913 --> 24:18.370
...I grew up
hearing a lot of four letter words...

24:18.541 --> 24:21.374
...and love wasn't exactly one of them.

24:21.585 --> 24:24.998
If you found it, real love...

24:25.923 --> 24:27.663
...hold onto it.

24:33.139 --> 24:36.802
And if anyone tells you that's a cliché,
I'll personally kick their ass.

24:39.145 --> 24:41.352
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

25:04.461 --> 25:05.541
[DOOR OPENS]

25:06.547 --> 25:08.538
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

25:10.634 --> 25:12.010
Did you ﬁnd her?

25:12.178 --> 25:14.089
She's gone off the grid again.

25:15.598 --> 25:17.759
Don't come back until you do.

25:23.105 --> 25:24.390
Is there something else?

25:24.690 --> 25:25.770
The girl's dangerous.

25:25.941 --> 25:29.183
You tried to approach her on the bus
and she blew it up.

25:29.361 --> 25:32.774
Mr. Luthor would've had us
terminate the problem on sight.

25:34.700 --> 25:36.406
I'm your boss now.

25:36.577 --> 25:38.283
And since we've never worked together...

25:38.454 --> 25:41.912
...I can't trust that you'll see this through
to my satisfaction.

25:42.166 --> 25:45.579
Bring her here, I'll handle her.

25:45.753 --> 25:47.618
End of story.

26:03.354 --> 26:05.811
Lois, you can't just walk in
and steal a ﬁle.

26:05.981 --> 26:08.814
-lt's a crime, you'll go to prison.
-I have a plan, Clark.

26:08.984 --> 26:11.145
Would you like to share it?
I'm having doubts.

26:11.320 --> 26:12.309
[LOIS SIGHS]

26:12.488 --> 26:14.149
When in doubt...

26:14.323 --> 26:15.984
...charge it.

26:16.408 --> 26:20.321
City Hall, 13th Precinct, 15th Precinct...

26:20.496 --> 26:22.657
...Metropolis General.

26:24.375 --> 26:27.082
If I could get mileage points on these,
I'd see the world.

26:27.670 --> 26:29.706
Cover me, Smallville.

26:32.633 --> 26:33.622
[SIGHS]

26:40.516 --> 26:43.553
Uh, you know, patients are on
an entirely different ﬂoor.

26:43.727 --> 26:47.094
You know, I thought I got off
the elevator a little early.

26:47.690 --> 26:50.602
Wait, you were one of the rescue workers
from the bus, right?

26:50.776 --> 26:52.186
I thought I recognized you.

26:52.361 --> 26:54.898
For a guy without a uniform,
you helped a lot of people.

26:55.281 --> 26:56.612
Oh, I didn't do anything.

26:56.782 --> 26:58.773
I mean, you're the real hero.

26:59.201 --> 27:00.657
You help people for a living.

27:01.287 --> 27:02.823
I'm Clark Kent.

27:02.997 --> 27:08.117
Davis Bloom. I met your ﬁancee, Clark.
Congratulations, she's a real catch.

27:08.627 --> 27:09.707
I'm getting married?

27:10.421 --> 27:11.581
Well, I thought that--

27:11.755 --> 27:14.212
I saw you and Chloe together.
And you seemed pretty close.

27:14.383 --> 27:17.216
-When she said she was engaged—
-Chloe's engaged?

27:17.803 --> 27:20.545
Oh, man. Okay, my brain's gone
completely DOA.

27:20.723 --> 27:24.056
Clark, she said
she hadn't told anyone yet.

27:24.226 --> 27:25.841
Do me a favor...

27:26.020 --> 27:28.557
...don't tell her I said anything.

27:30.274 --> 27:31.730
I won't reveal my source.

27:32.151 --> 27:33.231
[DOOR CLOSES]

27:38.073 --> 27:40.860
Hey, Bette. Davis, the paramedic
we met on the street...

27:41.035 --> 27:42.616
...came by with the paperwork.

27:42.786 --> 27:44.492
His friends wanna meet you.

27:44.663 --> 27:47.450
Change of plan, Chloe.
I'm leaving Metropolis.

27:47.624 --> 27:51.208
Don't you think that you should read
this ﬁrst? This place sounds great.

27:51.378 --> 27:52.538
Maybe it is.

27:52.713 --> 27:54.123
This city's gone sour.

27:54.298 --> 27:56.789
Like, way past its shelf life.
I have to go.

27:56.967 --> 27:58.958
Look, I know what happened
with Tommy was awful...

27:59.136 --> 28:01.502
...but running away is not the answer.

28:01.680 --> 28:04.763
Besides, it's not safe out there
for you by yourself.

28:04.933 --> 28:06.469
You think the street's dangerous?

28:06.643 --> 28:09.259
Try a locked door,
with someone else holding the key.

28:09.438 --> 28:11.349
-No, thanks.
-They're not gonna lock you in.

28:11.523 --> 28:13.775
-l'|l call them for you.
-Chloe, stop.

28:13.942 --> 28:16.775
I don't need a den mother,
and I won't go see those people.

28:16.945 --> 28:18.071
Then they'll come here.

28:18.238 --> 28:20.729
-You're not listening to me.
-l'm just trying to help you.

28:27.831 --> 28:30.538
I wish you hadn't made me do that.

28:36.632 --> 28:38.088
[SIREN WAILS]

28:44.640 --> 28:46.801
There's nothing in here
about a meteor infection.

28:46.975 --> 28:49.887
-Here. Let me take a look.
-Knock yourself out.

28:50.312 --> 28:52.143
I'm not sure we're on the right
track, Lois.

28:52.314 --> 28:55.101
-Tommy's death seems suspicious.
-Of course it's suspicious.

28:55.275 --> 28:59.063
The guy blew himself up by rubbing
his hands together or wrinkling his nose.

28:59.238 --> 29:03.072
They didn't ﬁnd any meteor rock in his
system but they did ﬁnd metal shrapnel.

29:03.242 --> 29:05.278
If Tommy's responsible for the blast...

29:05.452 --> 29:07.989
...the barrels would have blown away,
not into him.

29:08.163 --> 29:09.824
Don't clear his name yet, Sherlock.

29:09.998 --> 29:13.240
That kid was dangerous, a live wire.
Check his rap sheet at the back.

29:13.419 --> 29:15.410
Armed robbery, B&E and carjacking.

29:15.587 --> 29:18.169
That ﬁrecracker
was a major menace to Metropolis.

29:18.340 --> 29:20.922
There's no mention of explosives
in any of these crimes.

29:21.093 --> 29:23.926
If you were a criminal with abilities,
wouldn't you use them?

29:24.346 --> 29:26.462
If Tommy didn't kill himself,
then who did?

29:27.433 --> 29:30.175
Bette claimed
that Tommy blew up the bus.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.305
But she was there for both of the blasts.

29:33.981 --> 29:37.690
Oh, my God.
My cousin's babysitting Psycho Spice.

29:39.653 --> 29:41.484
Clark, what if--?

29:42.489 --> 29:44.354
Oh, come on.

29:45.451 --> 29:47.191
Believe me, I understand.

29:47.369 --> 29:51.032
It can be tough to control your powers
when you're angry or afraid.

29:51.206 --> 29:53.458
Like on the bus...

29:53.625 --> 29:54.705
...or with Tommy.

29:54.877 --> 29:56.538
Those weren't accidents.

29:56.712 --> 29:59.203
I knew what I was doing.

29:59.465 --> 30:01.581
There are some bad people chasing me.

30:01.758 --> 30:04.295
They cornered me on the bus,
I had to ﬁght back.

30:04.761 --> 30:07.013
So you set up Tommy to take the blame?

30:08.307 --> 30:09.717
Bette...

30:10.058 --> 30:11.594
...you killed him.

30:11.768 --> 30:14.305
He helped them ﬁnd me.

30:15.022 --> 30:19.561
Three years ago, some corporate
types locked me in their private prison.

30:19.902 --> 30:23.895
It was a nightmare.
They ran tests on me every day.

30:24.072 --> 30:26.484
Last week something happened,
and we were all let go.

30:27.993 --> 30:30.359
They tagged us on the way out.

30:30.871 --> 30:33.362
I ran before they could do it to me.

30:33.540 --> 30:35.872
This place, were there
lots of people with powers?

30:36.043 --> 30:37.123
Yeah.

30:37.294 --> 30:39.034
I told Tommy all about it.

30:39.213 --> 30:40.749
And you know what he did?

30:40.923 --> 30:43.084
He sold me out.

30:43.258 --> 30:45.465
He led them straight to me.

30:45.636 --> 30:47.843
He got what he deserved.

30:48.805 --> 30:52.593
The prison was in Montana, wasn't it?
Black Creek?

30:53.018 --> 30:55.100
How did you know that?

30:57.356 --> 30:59.347
Because I was there.

30:59.525 --> 31:01.436
I had a meteor power too.

31:01.610 --> 31:04.522
I could heal people.
I know how awful it was there.

31:04.863 --> 31:08.981
You know I had to do whatever it took to
get away. They had me backed in a corner.

31:10.285 --> 31:13.743
No matter what they do to you, Bette,
you don't kill people.

31:17.251 --> 31:19.287
Chloe, I'm sorry.

31:19.461 --> 31:21.827
But I can't risk you turning on me too.

31:26.802 --> 31:28.508
Goodbye, Chloe.

31:29.471 --> 31:32.178
-Aah!
-No.

31:41.650 --> 31:43.811
[CHLOE PANTING]

31:44.403 --> 31:46.018
Clark.

31:46.363 --> 31:48.354
[PANTING]

31:49.992 --> 31:51.277
Stay away from me!

31:51.451 --> 31:52.577
I'll hurt you!

31:52.744 --> 31:54.120
No, you won't.

31:54.913 --> 31:58.076
-You're not afraid of me?
-No.

31:58.250 --> 32:00.332
I just wanna help you.

32:01.169 --> 32:03.125
After everything I've done...

32:03.297 --> 32:05.754
...why would you wanna help
a monster like me?

32:05.924 --> 32:07.789
Because you're not a monster.

32:07.968 --> 32:10.584
You've just been led
down the wrong path.

32:12.514 --> 32:14.550
Whenever people ﬁnd out about me...

32:14.725 --> 32:17.717
...they get afraid and they try to hurt me.

32:18.020 --> 32:21.638
So I have to lie. I have to hide what I am.

32:23.692 --> 32:25.683
You don't have to anymore.

32:26.528 --> 32:27.813
Not from me.

32:39.207 --> 32:41.823
We all have something
we think we need to hide.

32:43.795 --> 32:45.581
It's hard.

32:48.216 --> 32:49.547
But it does get better.

33:00.729 --> 33:01.809
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

33:03.523 --> 33:04.558
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

33:04.733 --> 33:07.520
It's a good thing you called Lois
and told her you were okay.

33:07.694 --> 33:09.434
She was about to call out
the National Guard.

33:09.613 --> 33:10.773
[SIREN WAILS]

33:10.947 --> 33:12.733
[VEHICLE DEPARTS]

33:12.908 --> 33:15.399
Bette almost killed me, Clark.

33:16.328 --> 33:19.240
Chloe, there's no way you could've known
how dangerous she was.

33:19.414 --> 33:20.950
Her power was hidden.

33:21.625 --> 33:24.958
Some sort of high-frequency energy blast.
She fooled everyone.

33:25.420 --> 33:26.921
Because she didn't trust anyone.

33:27.089 --> 33:29.330
I was only in that cell for a few weeks.

33:29.508 --> 33:32.841
I can't imagine being in there
for three years.

33:33.011 --> 33:35.502
She'll ﬁnd the help she needs
at Belle Reve.

33:35.681 --> 33:40.050
I seriously doubt that being locked away
in another cell is gonna do any good.

33:41.061 --> 33:43.848
Do you think if you knew her sooner,
you could've helped her?

33:44.106 --> 33:46.017
Sometimes people
who need help the most...

33:46.191 --> 33:47.897
...are the ones who push it away.

33:48.151 --> 33:50.984
Which is why someone
should be talking to them from day one.

33:59.246 --> 34:00.952
Looking for this?

34:02.374 --> 34:06.868
I found it downstairs. You must have lost it
when Bette was chasing you.

34:11.633 --> 34:15.467
-ls there anything you wanna tell me?
-I was...

34:15.637 --> 34:18.754
...on my way over here this morning,
to tell you but—

34:21.268 --> 34:22.633
How did you ﬁnd out?

34:22.811 --> 34:24.267
Did Jimmy call you?

34:25.772 --> 34:30.812
Well, it's rule number 11.
Always protect your source.

34:30.986 --> 34:32.101
[CHUCKLES]

34:34.489 --> 34:36.980
But I would like the whole story.

34:38.994 --> 34:41.326
How long have you been engaged?

34:42.330 --> 34:44.195
A week.

34:44.458 --> 34:47.416
I said yes
the night I came back from Montana.

34:48.295 --> 34:49.535
[CLARK SIGHS]

34:49.713 --> 34:51.294
You could have called...

34:51.465 --> 34:52.705
...anytime.

34:54.509 --> 34:56.374
It's just that...

34:57.387 --> 35:00.345
...we've been friends
for such a long time.

35:00.932 --> 35:03.218
We're more than just friends, Chloe.

35:07.731 --> 35:10.222
When Jimmy and I get married...

35:10.525 --> 35:13.232
...things will probably change...

35:13.403 --> 35:15.860
...between us, I mean.

35:18.116 --> 35:21.199
And I don't know
if I'm ready for that just yet.

35:23.038 --> 35:24.118
Are you?

35:30.921 --> 35:34.209
Your happiness is one of the most
important things in the world to me.

35:35.383 --> 35:38.375
And you and Jimmy
will have a wonderful life together.

35:44.184 --> 35:46.095
Don't worry about anything else.

36:20.428 --> 36:22.384
TESS:
Hello, Bette.

36:24.099 --> 36:26.681
You should've died on that bus.

36:28.770 --> 36:32.604
The last time we met,
things did get a little ﬁery.

36:32.774 --> 36:34.730
Lucky for me I ducked.

36:37.737 --> 36:40.649
So they're taking you to Belle Reve.

36:41.449 --> 36:43.610
I'm sure after a few years
of good behavior...

36:43.785 --> 36:46.117
...they'll let you see the sun again.

36:46.705 --> 36:48.741
Or you could come with me.

36:49.457 --> 36:53.575
I'd rather be a prisoner there
than your lab rat in Montana.

36:53.753 --> 36:55.789
Go push your cheese somewhere else.

37:05.557 --> 37:08.219
I didn't build that place, Bette.

37:08.435 --> 37:11.393
After I heard about
all the terrible things happening there...

37:11.563 --> 37:13.599
...I closed it down.

37:13.773 --> 37:14.808
I tried to tell you.

37:15.984 --> 37:19.647
If you shut down the Thunderdome,
then why are you still coming after me?

37:21.448 --> 37:24.485
Because you're a very powerful person.

37:27.037 --> 37:30.871
And I think it's about time
the world started treated you accordingly.

37:31.041 --> 37:32.121
Don't you?

37:34.002 --> 37:35.367
Listening.

37:36.671 --> 37:38.662
I want to introduce you...

37:38.840 --> 37:41.877
...to some people like you.

37:42.052 --> 37:44.213
A sort of team.

37:44.387 --> 37:45.843
But only if you want.

37:46.014 --> 37:47.174
A team?

37:47.349 --> 37:50.807
Take a look at my ﬁle, lady.
I don't play well with others.

37:51.478 --> 37:54.686
I think once you meet everyone,
you may ﬁnally feel like you ﬁt in.

37:56.775 --> 37:59.858
I remember what it was like
to be your age.

38:00.195 --> 38:01.901
Alone...

38:02.197 --> 38:04.062
...angry...

38:05.116 --> 38:07.027
...trapped.

38:07.535 --> 38:10.151
The injustice of it all.

38:11.206 --> 38:13.822
I can help, Bette.

38:17.087 --> 38:20.204
The team is only as good
as its weakest link.

38:20.382 --> 38:23.215
And look at what happened to me
on the bus.

38:24.177 --> 38:27.089
Why scout out somebody
who's gonna choke on their own smoke?

38:28.556 --> 38:31.389
Don't be so hard on yourself.

38:35.563 --> 38:37.895
We'll make a hero out of you yet.

38:47.617 --> 38:49.733
MAN:
That was a great job.

38:57.585 --> 39:02.045
Looking good, Smallville. Clothes make the
man who helped me make the front page.

39:02.674 --> 39:03.914
[CLARK CLEARS THROAT]

39:04.092 --> 39:06.083
Wow. Try to hold back
the journalistic fervor.

39:06.261 --> 39:09.924
I'm glad you got your story, but it
took more turns than I would have liked.

39:10.098 --> 39:12.510
So did you, Houdini. You're there
one minute, gone the next.

39:12.684 --> 39:15.096
We're standing next to an elevator.
Why take stairs?

39:15.270 --> 39:17.932
Well, I'm sorry that you can't keep up.

39:18.106 --> 39:21.189
The important thing is,
Chloe ﬁgured it out and she's okay.

39:21.609 --> 39:24.772
Yeah, tell me about it. If she hadn't defused
Little Miss Landmine...

39:24.946 --> 39:27.858
...we'd be ﬁtting her for a cofﬁn
instead of a wedding dress.

39:29.659 --> 39:31.320
When did you hear about the wedding?

39:31.661 --> 39:33.367
She just called.

39:33.538 --> 39:36.154
I can't believe my cousin
is getting married.

39:36.332 --> 39:38.459
To Jimmy Olsen.

39:39.294 --> 39:40.784
They're in love, Lois.

39:40.962 --> 39:42.623
You should be happy for them.

39:42.797 --> 39:44.753
Uh, well...

39:44.924 --> 39:46.710
...at least the rest of us have work.

39:46.885 --> 39:50.127
Here, I ﬁnished prooﬁng the obit.

39:51.639 --> 39:53.675
Well, Lois, don't hold anything back.

39:53.892 --> 39:56.804
Those aren't notes of discouragement.
They're of encouragement.

39:56.978 --> 39:59.014
You've got talent, Smallville.

39:59.189 --> 40:00.770
What?

40:00.940 --> 40:03.647
When I started at the Inquisitor,
all I cared about...

40:03.818 --> 40:06.104
...was getting the best stories
on the front page.

40:06.279 --> 40:07.940
It seems like a dream come true.

40:08.656 --> 40:11.489
Sure, but sitting here now, with you...

40:11.659 --> 40:16.449
...I think I'm more proud we uncovered the
truth than I am over having a headline.

40:21.336 --> 40:24.043
Thanks for helping me
break the story, Clark.

40:27.133 --> 40:28.919
Keep up the good work.

40:29.094 --> 40:32.336
You've got a long career
ahead of you at the Daily Planet.

40:56.037 --> 40:57.743
[PHONE DIALING]

40:59.624 --> 41:02.331
[LINE RINGING]

41:04.045 --> 41:07.333
DAVIS [ON MACHINE]: Hey, this is Davis.
Leave me your story, I'll call you back.

41:07.507 --> 41:08.792
[MACHINE BEEPS]

41:08.967 --> 41:11.379
CHLOE:
Hi, Davis. It's Chloe Sullivan.

41:11.553 --> 41:12.838
I, uh--

41:13.012 --> 41:17.381
I just wanted to call and say thanks
for helping out with Bette.

41:17.559 --> 41:21.222
It's too bad that
that didn't, uh, work out...

41:21.729 --> 41:23.560
...but I also wanted
to let you know...

41:23.731 --> 41:26.814
...that I've decided to reopen
the Isis Foundation.

41:26.985 --> 41:30.773
And a few things that you said
helped me make that decision.

41:30.947 --> 41:32.562
So thanks. Heh.

41:32.782 --> 41:34.898
Okay, well...

41:35.076 --> 41:36.532
...stay safe out there.

41:36.703 --> 41:38.318
Take care.

41:53.761 --> 41:54.921
[GASPS]

42:29.797 --> 42:31.788
[ENGLISH SDH]
